  <Name>k__BackingField: 1 Timothy
  fancyName: 
  nickname: 1ti
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Greeting'
      title: Greeting
      number: 1
      content: ' Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus according to the command of God
        our Savior and of Christ Jesus our hope, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Instructions for Timothy in Ephesus'
      title: Instructions for Timothy in Ephesus
      number: 2
      content: 'to Timothy, my true child in the faith. Grace, mercy, and peace from
        God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Just as I urged you when I traveled to Macedonia, remain in Ephesus,
        so that you may instruct certain people not to teach other doctrine, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and not to pay attention to myths and endless genealogies, which
        cause useless speculations rather than God\u2019s plan that is by faith. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the goal of our instruction is love from a pure heart and a good
        conscience and a faith without hypocrisy, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'from which some have deviated, and have turned away into fruitless
        discussion, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'wanting to be teachers of the law, although they do not understand
        either the things which they are saying or the things concerning which they
        are speaking confidently. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But we know that the law is good, if anyone makes use of it lawfully, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'knowing this, that the law is not given for a righteous person but
        for the lawless and rebellious, for the ungodly and sinners, for the unholy
        and totally worldly, for the one who kills his father and the one who kills
        his mother, for murderers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'sexually immoral people, homosexuals, kidnappers, liars, perjurers,
        and whatever else is opposed to sound teaching, '
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Paul\u2019s Thankfulness for the Mercy Shown to Him"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Thankfulness for the Mercy Shown to Him"
      number: 11
      content: 'according to the glorious gospel of the blessed God that I was entrusted
        with. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I give thanks to the one who strengthens me, Christ Jesus our Lord,
        because he considered me faithful, placing me into ministry,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'although I was formerly a blasphemer and a persecutor and a violent
        man, but I was shown mercy because I acted ignorantly in unbelief, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and the grace of our Lord abounded with the faith and love that are
        in Christ Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The saying is trustworthy and worthy of all acceptance: Christ Jesus
        came into the world to save sinners, of whom I am the foremost. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But because of this I was shown mercy, in order that in me foremost,
        Christ Jesus might demonstrate his total patience, for an example for those
        who are going to believe in him for eternal life. '
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Paul\u2019s Charge to Timothy"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Charge to Timothy"
      number: 17
      content: 'Now to the King of the ages, immortal, invisible, to the only God,
        be honor and glory forever and ever. Amen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I am setting before you this instruction, Timothy my child, in accordance
        with the prophecies spoken long ago about you, in order that by them you
        may fight the good fight, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'having faith and a good conscience, which some, because they have
        rejected these, have suffered shipwreck concerning their faith, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'among whom are Hymenaeus and Alexander, whom I have handed over to
        Satan, in order that they may be taught not to blaspheme. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Instructions to Pray for All People'
      title: Instructions to Pray for All People
      number: 1
      content: ' Therefore, I urge first of all that petitions, prayers, requests,
        and thanksgiving be made on behalf of all people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'on behalf of kings and all those who are in authority, in order that
        we may live a tranquil and quiet life in all godliness and dignity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'This is good and acceptable before God our Savior, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'who wants all people to be saved and to come to a knowledge of the
        truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For there is one God and one mediator between God and human beings,
        the man Christ Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'who gave himself a ransom for all, the testimony at the proper time, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "for which I was appointed a herald and an apostle\u2014I am speaking
        the truth, I am not lying\u2014a teacher of the Gentiles in faith and truth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Instructions for Women'
      title: Instructions for Women
      number: 8
      content: 'Therefore I want the men in every place to pray, lifting up holy
        hands without anger and dispute. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Likewise also the women should adorn themselves in appropriate clothing,
        with modesty and self-control, not with braided hair and gold jewelry or
        pearls or expensive clothing, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but with good deeds which are fitting for women who profess godliness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'A woman must learn in quietness with all submission. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But I do not permit a woman to teach or to exercise authority over
        a man, but to remain quiet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For Adam was formed first, then Eve, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and Adam was not deceived, but the woman, because she was deceived,
        came into transgression. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But she will be saved through the bearing of children, if she continues
        in faith and love and holiness with self-control. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Qualifications for Overseers'
      title: Qualifications for Overseers
      number: 1
      content: ' The saying is trustworthy: if anyone aspires to supervision, he
        desires a good work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Therefore the overseer must be irreproachable, the husband of one
        wife, temperate, self-controlled, respectable, hospitable, skillful in teaching, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'not addicted to wine, not a violent person, but gentle, peaceable,
        not loving money, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'managing his own household well, having children in submission with
        all dignity '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '(but if someone does not know how to manage his own household, how
        will he take care of the church of God?), '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'not newly converted, lest he become conceited and fall into the condemnation
        of the devil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Qualifications for Deacons'
      title: Qualifications for Deacons
      number: 7
      content: 'But he must also have a good testimony from those outside, in order
        that he may not fall into disgrace and the trap of the devil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Deacons likewise must be dignified, not insincere, not devoted to
        much wine, not fond of dishonest gain, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'holding the mystery of the faith with a clear conscience, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and these also must be tested first; then let them serve if they
        are above reproach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The wives likewise must be dignified, not slanderous, temperate,
        faithful in all things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Deacons must be husbands of one wife, managing their children and
        their own households well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Mystery of Godliness Described'
      title: The Mystery of Godliness Described
      number: 13
      content: 'For those who have served well acquire a good standing for themselves,
        and great boldness in the faith that is in Christ Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I am writing these things to you, hoping to come to you in a short
        time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But if I am delayed, I am writing in order that you may know how
        one must conduct oneself in the household of God, which is the church of
        the living God, the pillar and mainstay of the truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And most certainly, great is the mystery of godliness: Who was revealed
        in the flesh, was vindicated by the Spirit, was seen by angels, was proclaimed
        among the Gentiles, was believed on in the world, was taken up in glory. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Coming Apostasy'
      title: The Coming Apostasy
      number: 1
      content: ' Now the Spirit explicitly says that in the last times some will
        depart from the faith, paying attention to deceitful spirits and teachings
        of demons, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'by the hypocrisy of liars, who are seared in their own conscience, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'who forbid marrying and insist on abstaining from foods that God
        created for sharing in with thankfulness by those who believe and who know
        the truth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'because everything created by God is good and nothing is to be rejected
        if it is received with thankfulness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Good Servant of Christ'
      title: The Good Servant of Christ
      number: 5
      content: 'for it is made holy by the word of God and prayer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'By teaching these things to the brothers, you will be a good servant
        of Christ Jesus, trained in the words of the faith and of the good teaching
        that you have followed faithfully. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But reject those worthless myths told by elderly women, and train
        yourself for godliness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the training of the body is somewhat profitable, but godliness
        is profitable for everything, because it holds promise for the present life
        and for the life to come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The statement is trustworthy and deserving of complete acceptance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For to this end we labor and suffer reproach, because we have put
        our hope in the living God, who is the Savior of all people, especially of
        believers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Command these things and teach them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let no one look down on your youth, but be an example for the believers
        in word, in conduct, in love, in faith, in purity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Until I come, pay attention to the public reading, to exhortation,
        to teaching. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Do not neglect the gift that is in you, that was granted to you through
        prophecy with the laying on of hands by the council of elders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Practice these things. Be diligent in these things, in order that
        your progress may be evident to everyone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Fix your attention on yourself and on your teaching. Continue in
        them, for by doing this you will save both yourself and those who hear you. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Instructions About Widows'
      title: Instructions About Widows
      number: 1
      content: ' Do not rebuke an older man, but appeal to him as a father, younger
        men as brothers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'older women as mothers, younger women as sisters, with all purity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Honor widows who are truly widows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But if any widow has children or grandchildren, they must learn to
        show profound respect for their own household first, and to pay back recompense
        to their parents, for this is pleasing in the sight of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the widow who is one truly, and is left alone, has put her hope
        in God and continues in her petitions and prayers night and day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But the one who lives for sensual pleasure is dead even though she
        lives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And command these things, in order that they may be irreproachable. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But if someone does not provide for his own relatives, and especially
        the members of his household, he has denied the faith and is worse than an
        unbeliever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Let a widow be put on the list if she is not less than sixty years
        old, the wife of one husband, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'being well-attested by good works, if she has brought up children,
        if she has shown hospitality, if she has washed the feet of the saints, if
        she has helped those who are oppressed, if she has devoted herself to every
        good work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But refuse younger widows, for whenever their physical desires lead
        them away from Christ, they want to marry, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'thus incurring condemnation because they have broken their former
        pledge. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And at the same time also, going around from house to house, they
        learn to be idle, and not only idle, but also gossipy and busybodies, saying
        the things that are not necessary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore I want younger widows to marry, to bear children, to manage
        a household, to give the adversary no opportunity for reproach. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For already some have turned away and followed after Satan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Honoring Worthy Elders and Dealing With Sinners'
      title: Honoring Worthy Elders and Dealing With Sinners
      number: 16
      content: 'If any believing woman has widows, she must help them, and the church
        must not be burdened, in order that it may help those who are truly widows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The elders who lead well must be considered worthy of double honor,
        especially those who labor by speaking and teaching. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For the scripture says, \u201CYou must not muzzle an ox while it
        is threshing,\u201D and \u201CThe worker is worthy of his wages.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Do not accept an accusation against an elder except on the evidence
        of two or three witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Reprove those who sin in the presence of all, in order that the rest
        also may experience fear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'I testify solemnly before God and Christ Jesus and the elect angels
        that you observe these things without prejudice, doing nothing according
        to partiality. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Lay hands on no one hastily, and do not participate in the sins of
        others. Keep yourself pure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '(No longer drink only water, but use a little wine for your stomach
        and your frequent illnesses.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The sins of some people are evident, preceding them to judgment,
        but for some also they follow after them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Likewise also good works are evident, and those considered otherwise
        are not able to be hidden. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Slaves and Masters'
      title: Slaves and Masters
      number: 1
      content: ' All those who are under the yoke as slaves must regard their own
        masters as worthy of all honor, lest the name of God and the teaching be
        slandered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: False Teachers and the Love of Money'
      title: False Teachers and the Love of Money
      number: 2
      content: 'And those who have believing masters must not look down on them because
        they are brothers, but rather they must serve, because those who benefit
        by their service are believers and dearly loved. Teach and encourage these
        things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'If anyone teaches other doctrine and does not devote himself to the
        sound words of our Lord Jesus Christ and the teaching that is in accordance
        with godliness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'he is conceited, understanding nothing, but having a morbid interest
        concerning controversies and disputes about words, from which come envy,
        strife, slanders, evil suspicions, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'constant wrangling by people of depraved mind and deprived of the
        truth, who consider godliness to be a means of gain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But godliness with contentment is a great means of gain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For we have brought nothing into the world, so that neither can we
        bring anything out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But if we have food and clothing, with these things we will be content. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But those who want to be rich fall into temptation and a trap and
        many foolish and harmful desires, which plunge those people into ruin and
        destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Renewed Charge to Timothy'
      title: Renewed Charge to Timothy
      number: 10
      content: 'For the love of money is a root of all evil, by which some, because
        they desire it, have gone astray from the faith and have pierced themselves
        with many pains. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But you, O man of God, flee from these things, and pursue righteousness,
        godliness, faith, love, patient endurance, gentleness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Fight the good fight of the faith; take hold of the eternal life
        to which you were called, and confessed the good confession in the presence
        of many witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I command you, in the sight of God who gives life to all things and
        Christ Jesus who testified the good confession before Pontius Pilate, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'that you observe the commandment without fault, irreproachable until
        the appearing of our Lord Jesus Christ, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'which he will make known in his own time, the blessed and only Sovereign,
        the King of those who reign as kings and Lord of those who rule as lords, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Instructions to the Rich'
      title: Instructions to the Rich
      number: 16
      content: 'the one who alone possesses immortality, who lives in unapproachable
        light, whom no human being has seen nor is able to see, to whom be honor
        and eternal power. Amen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Command those who are rich in this present age not to be proud and
        not to put their hope in the uncertainty of riches, but in God, who provides
        us all things richly for enjoyment, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'to do good, to be rich in good works, to be generous, sharing freely, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Final Charge and Benediction'
      title: Final Charge and Benediction
      number: 19
      content: 'storing up for themselves a good foundation for the future, in order
        that they may take hold of what is truly life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'O Timothy, guard what has been entrusted to you. Turn away from pointless
        empty talk and contradictions of what is falsely called knowledge, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'which some, by professing it, have deviated concerning the faith.
        Grace be with you all. '
      comments: []
